<h2>Make standard messages accessible</h2>
<p class="nhsuk-body">Aim to make all the text messages, emails and App messages you send accessible to people who:</p>
<ul>
  <li>use assistive technology, like a screen reader</li>
  <li>have a low level of literacy</li>
  <li>have low numeracy</li>
  <li>have a learning difficulty or autism</li>
  <li>have co-ordination difficulties</li>
  <li>do not speak English as their first language</li>
</ul>
<p>This will reduce the number of messages you need to send in alternative formats (also known as accessible formats).</p>
<p>Follow the <a href="/content/how-we-write">How we write section of our content guide</a> to write messages that are:</p>
<ul>
  <li>clear and in plain English, so someone with a reading age of 9 to 11 years can understand them</li>
  <li>concise, with short sentences and paragraphs</li>
  <li>in the active voice, not passive voice</li>
</ul>
